  "texts": [
    "Moreover, we faced difficulties in accessing high-level executives and board members from large companies.",
    "Their insights would have been invaluable, especially regarding strategic decisions and the adoption of AI at the highest levels of organizations.",
    "Additionally, the majority of participants were based in the Netherlands, which may not fully represent the broader European or international context.Another limitation is that our study was conducted at a single point in time.",
    "Especially regarding the influence of regulations, a longitudinal study might provide much more reliable and detailed results.",
    "This limited our ability to observe the long-term impacts of the EU AI Act.Finally, the popularity or desirability of AI may have influenced the participants' responses, particularly concerning sustainability awareness and efforts."
